div.page-header
    h1 5P49V5901 (VersaClockÂ® 5) Custom Part Configuration Utility
    p The 5P49V5901 features one flexible input and four programmable outputs. The device can store up to four configurations selectable using the SEL pins. Use the form below to configure outputs for each configuration used. <br/>IMPORTANT NOTE: In order to minimize sample delivery times, all outputs will be configured to provide RMS phase jitter performance of 1.5 ps or less (12 kHz to 20 MHz integration range). If lower phase jitter is required, please provide the requirements in the comment box located at the bottom of this form.

#global-configuration.col-xs-12.col-md-6.center-block
    form
        div.form-group
            label Configurations
            |<select class="form-control" required [(ngModel)] = "settings.configurationCount">
            |   <option *ngFor="#conf of settings.configurationCount_options.options" [value]="conf">{{conf}}</option>
            |</select>

        div.form-group
            label I2C Address
            |<select class="form-control" required [(ngModel)] = "settings.i2cAddress">
            |    <option *ngFor="#addr of settings.i2cAddress_options.options" [value]="addr">{{addr}}</option>
            |</select>

        div.form-group
            label Crystal Load Capacitance(pF)
            |<select class=form-control required [(ngModel)] = "settings.crystalLoadCap">
            |    <option *ngFor="#loadCap of settings.crystalLoadCap_options.options" [value]="loadCap">{{loadCap}}</option>
            |</select>

        div.form-group
            label Free Entry Test
            div.input-group
                | <input class=form-control required [(ngModel)] = "test" ngControl="testName" #testName="ngForm"/>
                span.input-group-btn
                    button.btn.btn-toolbarc details
            |<div [hidden]="testName.valid || testName.pristine" class="alert alert-danger">Free Entry Test is required</div>


        button.btn.btn-default(type="submit") Next Step